.el .ds Aq '
.TH pif-config-verbose 1  "pif-config-verbose " 
.SH NAME
pif\-config\-verbose \- Manage the verbosity level
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpif\-config\-verbose\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage the verbosity level
.PP
Persists the verbosity preference to the config file so that the chosen level becomes the default for all future pif invocations. Override for a single run with the global \-\-verbose flag.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
pif\-config\-verbose\-set(1)
Persist a verbosity level to the config file
.TP
pif\-config\-verbose\-reset(1)
Reset the verbosity level to the built\-in default (2)
.TP
pif\-config\-verbose\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
